Only relatively speaking do we &quot;lose&quot; anything (and I use the term loosely).<br>
<br>
eg, hybrids dodge was 150 pre patch, warriors was 175 - hybrids had 88.2% of warrior dodge ability. Hybrids now have 170 and warriors have 190 - hybrids now have 89.5% of warrior dodge ability.<br>
<br>
So, relatively speaking warriors &quot;lost&quot; some of the tanking advantage we had over knights, namely 1.3%-points difference (from 11.8% to 10.5%).<br>
<br>
The effect is so very miniscule that you would need a microscope and a pair of nano-tweecers to be able to find it, unless there is some kind of &quot;cap&quot; on dodge that the hybrids just gets over from 150-170 that warriors were over before, and there is no new &quot;cap&quot; from 175-190, pure speculation this.<br>
<br>
To recap, the change has done neglible difference to the relative difference in hybrid vs. warrior avoidance, certainly not enough to warrant an outcry of this proportion.<br>
